"v.闲荡，虚度 【英】 v. 闲荡，虚度 (to waste time in trifling ; idle; loiter) 【考】 反义词：hie(催促, 急忙) 【同】 派生词: dawdler(n. 闲逛者) 【例】 He dawdled all morning. v. (漫无目的地、懒洋洋地)闲荡; 虚度(浪费时间) = idle = loiter 【记】读: 兜兜, 即饭后的兜兜弯－闲逛 【参】dawdler(n 闲逛者; 游手好闲的人) 【反】hie(v 催促; 急忙) 【记】音：踱 + idle→悠闲的踱步；dawn + idle 一天到晚空闲，闲逛到黎明 dawdle (v.)  1650s, perhaps a variant of daddle ""to walk unsteadily."" Perhaps influenced by daw, because the bird was regarded as sluggish and silly. Not in general use until c.1775. Related: Dawdled; dawdling."
